						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/International-fellowships-programme-for-West-African-students" title="International fellowships programme for West African students" alt="link">International fellowships programme for West African students</a></h2>

	
					<p>The International Fellowships Program (IFP) is a program supported by the Ford Foundation, and coordinated in West Africa by the AAU in collaboration with Pathfinder International in Nigeria and the West African Research Center (WARC) in Senegal. IFP provides fellowships for advanced study to exceptional individuals who will use their education to further development in their own countries and greater social and economic justice worldwide.The fellowships will be awarded to applicants from diverse backgrounds, including social groups and communities that lack systematic access to higher education. Applicants must be resident nationals or residents from Nigeria, Ghana or Senegal. <b>The deadline for application is the 29th of January 2010.</b></p>
							<p><span class="date">21/12/2009</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Fellowships-grants-calls/International-fellowships-programme-for-West-African-students">Read more...</a>
</div>
<br class="cl">
